txt.en: Hûrlub the Bellower seems like a gentle creature. He has asked you to defeat spiders in Maj Khibi.
Hûrlub the Bellower does not seem to be hostile at all. He is agitated by the barbs of what seems to be spiders.

'Many legs gone?

'You did for Hûrlub? You friend me now. Hûrlub is happy.

'Ask a thing of Hûrlub. You have.

'This thing? It is done. Hûrlub not need big swing. Old toy.'

'You fight good, small thing.

'You not afraid of Hûrlub. Maybe Hûrlub make friend?

'Many leg ones. Crawlies. So many, they bully me. Keep Hûrlub from food.

'Can small thing make many leg ones no more?'
The spiders should be less likely to bother Hûrlub now. You should speak to Hûrlub in Phadâl Bimai.\n\nPhadâl Bimai can be found at the northern coast of Jeb Khâtel.
